-- Samsung Elec Q4 chip margin up
-- 
-- Thu Jan 11, 2007 9:37pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/12/us-samsung-chips-idUSSEO23838520070112

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd. ( 005930.KS ), the world's biggest maker of memory chips, reported on Monday the operating profit margin of its semiconductor division rose to 31 percent in the fourth quarter from 26 percent in the third. 

 Samsung saw the shipments of its mainstay dynamic random access memory (DRAM) and NAND flash memory chips rising by 19 percent each from the third quarter.